(950, 271, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"c3e1c48\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"structure\":\"20\",\"margin\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"30\",\"right\":0,\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":0,\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"bb3e529\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"e78ccb5\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>Through hours of research, focus group meetings and expert\'s contribution we created a collection of comprehensive behavioral, academic and cognitive recommendations that are geared to help children overcome attention shortcomings and at times also teach them how to utilize their unique attentive profile to their advantage. These recommendations are featured in the teacher, parent and student reports.<\\/p><p>Each child performing the test will receive recommendations, even if the performance on the test was flawless. The right way to use these recommendations is to choose from the list just two to three recommendations at a time and try them out for fit, before moving to the next set of recommendations.<\\/p><p>We are always happy to hear your feedback and ideas on additional recommendations that work from your experience. Just get in touch with us <em><u>here<\\/u><\\/em> and let us know.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"428bbb2\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null,\"background_background\":\"classic\",\"background_image\":{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/axon.digitalim.co.il\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/12\\/\\u05d0\\u05e7\\u05e1\\u05d5\\u05df-\\u05e1\\u05e7\\u05d5\\u05dc.jpg\",\"id\":227},\"background_position\":\"top center\",\"background_repeat\":\"no-repeat\",\"background_size\":\"cover\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"6d68a1c\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"space_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":200}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"spacer\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"a73c785\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"structure\":\"20\",\"margin\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":0,\"bottom\":\"30\",\"left\":0,\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"1e6531d\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null,\"background_background\":\"classic\",\"background_image\":{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/axon.digitalim.co.il\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/12\\/childinclass.jpg\",\"id\":228},\"background_position\":\"top center\",\"background_repeat\":\"no-repeat\",\"background_size\":\"cover\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ebeac48\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"space_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":200}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"spacer\"}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"071d00a\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"f2ddf2d\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<h3>Using the system in a school setting<\\/h3><p>The AXON-School\\u2122 system is designed to be used for the entire school once a year. Were the system has been used so far we learn that the cycle of a batch of children performing the test is usually 30 minutes which includes a short intro made by the teacher, logging-in, running through the on-screen instructions, performing a short practice session and finally performing the test.<\\/p><p>This process is very easy to manage, as the system runs automatically through most of the session. As a teacher you will not require any unusual technical skills to operate the system.<\\/p><p>We recommend a maximum number of 20 children per batch, provided that each child has enough space to perform the test without overlooking the monitor of a neighboring child.<\\/p><p>Each child will require a dedicated internet connected PC, a monitor and a headset.<\\/p><p>Results are funneled into the system immediately and automatically.<\\/p>\",\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right