(1113, 320, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"a73c785\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"structure\":\"20\",\"margin\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":0,\"bottom\":\"30\",\"left\":0,\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"1e6531d\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null,\"background_background\":\"classic\",\"background_image\":{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/axon.digitalim.co.il\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/12\\/childinclass.jpg\",\"id\":228},\"background_position\":\"top center\",\"background_repeat\":\"no-repeat\",\"background_size\":\"cover\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ebeac48\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"space_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":200}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"spacer\"}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"071d00a\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"f2ddf2d\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<h3>Using the system in a school setting<\\/h3><p>The AXON-School\\u2122 system is designed to be used for the entire school once a year. Were the system has been used so far we learn that the cycle of a batch of children performing the test is usually 30 minutes which includes a short intro made by the teacher, logging-in, running through the on-screen instructions, performing a short practice session and finally performing the test.<\\/p><p>This process is very easy to manage, as the system runs automatically through most of the session. As a teacher you will not require any unusual technical skills to operate the system.<\\/p><p>We recommend a maximum number of 20 children per batch, provided that each child has enough space to perform the test without overlooking the monitor of a neighboring child.<\\/p><p>Each child will require a dedicated internet connected PC, a monitor and a headset.<\\/p><p>Results are funneled into the system immediately and automatically.<\\/p>\",\"_padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\