(250, 1, '2017-12-28 00:38:31', '2017-12-28 00:38:31', '<img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/pic_01.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" srcset=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/pic_01.jpg 550w, https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/pic_01-150x150.jpg 150w, https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/pic_01-300x300.jpg 300w\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"550\" />\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;\">Educational teams are challenged with influencing student achievements, taking care of their physical safety and support their psychological wellbeing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;\">Many overlook how critically important are attentional skills in light of these challenges. Inattention for example is often mistaken for classroom boredom and likewise Impulsivity is often wrongly regarded as a behavioral problem.</p>\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><b>AXON-School™</b> aims to change the perception of attentional skills at school by helping teachers and parents alike recognize the importance of these skills and how they are reflected in each specific child. AXON-School™ utilizes a test that once taken by the children creates an attentional profile of their individual performance, highlighting important information and suggesting ways to help them learn and function better at school and at home.</p>\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;\">A<b>XON-School™</b> can provide concrete evidence to support the educational team’s professional approach; to better understand children attentional needs and facilitate a parent-teacher communication on that matter.</p>', 'AXON-School™ general overview', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '150-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 00:38:31', '2017-12-28 00:38:31', '', 150, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/28/150-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(253, 1, '2017-12-28 00:43:54', '2017-12-28 00:43:54', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Once the children complete doing their test of attention the teacher can scan the list of children from within the system and assess their individual level of attentional capabilities. At this stage, if attentional difficulties are spotted, it will be suggested to refer the child to further diagnosis</p>		\n			<figure><img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/kid_1.png\" alt=\"kid_1\" title=\"kid_1\"></figure><h3>Emily, 7 years old</h3><p>Emily, seven years old isn’t coping with her homework; it is very hard for her. She is never at ease; she becomes impatient, acts impulsively and tends to fight with her siblings which causes tension and makes it difficult to have a quiet evening at home.  </p>		\n			<figure><img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/kid_2.png\" alt=\"kid_2\" title=\"kid_2\"></figure><h3>Roy, 6 years old</h3><p>Roy, six years old, started first grade this year. While still in kindergarten his teacher advised his parents that he is unable to sit still; he is always running around and endangering himself.\n<br>\n</p>		\n			<figure><img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/kid_3.png\" alt=\"kid_3\" title=\"kid_3\"></figure><h3>Andy, 8.5 years old</h3><p>Andy, eight-and-a-half years old, is a quiet child who and according to his parents, has difficulty completing tasks. Every little noise or movement can easily distract him and it is a challenge for him to return to the task at hand.</p>		\n		<p style=\"text-align: center;\">What is common in all these cases is the fact that these kids are dealing with difficulties maintaining their focus, behavior and attention, and might have ADHD (Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder).</p><p><strong>The system will automatically produce three reports for each child, these reports are associated with the child\'s Individual attention profile.</strong></p>		\n			<figure><a href=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Axon-School_Techers-report_example.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_3.png\" alt=\"icon_3\" title=\"icon_3\"></a></figure><h3><a href=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Axon-School_Techers-report_example.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">A teacher report</a></h3><p>With comparative results and suggested techniques that the teacher can implement in class for the specific child and that can assist his learning.\n<b>Click for an example &gt;&gt;</b></p>		\n			<figure><a href=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/409_parents_report-2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_4.png\" alt=\"icon_4\" title=\"icon_4\"></a></figure><h3><a href=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/409_parents_report-2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">A Parent report</a></h3><p>suggesting techniques parents can use at home to strengthen their child social and learning abilities.<br> <b>Click for an example &gt;&gt;</b><br></p>		\n			<figure><a href=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Axon-School_ParentStudent-report_example.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_5.png\" alt=\"icon_5\" title=\"icon_5\"></a></figure><h3><a href=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Axon-School_ParentStudent-report_example.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">A child report</a></h3><p>The third report goes to the child himself. This time, showing the child his strengths and weaknesses in regards to his attention, suggesting technics that could make a difference in his life. <br><b>Click for an example &gt;&gt;</b></p>		\n		<p>School Counselors have additional benefits from the system allowing them an aggregated view of the entire class and grade. For more information go to <em><u>School strategies</u></em>.</p><h3>School Strategies</h3><p>AXON-School™ integrates a comprehensive view of the entire classroom and of the entire grade. These can be especially useful for class behavioral and performance management by the teacher and for the same management on a grade level usually done by a school counselor. <br />Try to recall a class you have been teaching that were notorious around school for being very difficult and noisy, this could be a very frustrating class, and many teachers feel that they do not possess the right tools to deal with such a class. We know that the attentional profile of a class could be an important starting point for a change. Imagine that based on the test results you find out that around 40% of your students are Impulsive-Hyperactive, and that many of them are highly distracted by visual stimulation. This knowledge can dramatically change the way you perceive your class, and we even make suggestions on what could work better in such a case.</p><p><a href=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Axon-School-counselor-report.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> Click here for an example of such a report.</a></p>		\n		', 'The AXON-School TM system', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 00:43:54', '2017-12-28 00:43:54', '', 193, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/28/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
