ver responsive) – Measurement of the number of responses the student is making for each target.\r\nThe three indices above have been tested in a clinical trial of over 798 children, and were found to have an excellent sensitivity profile of 90% and Specificity of 86%.\r\n<h2>Non-Comparative indices:</h2>\r\nThe AXON-School™ test makes use of several non-comparative indices related to the performance of the examinee throughout the test in relation to his base performance. This allows us to examine the impact of distractors and time on the student overall performance.\r\n<h3>Visual Distractibility</h3>\r\na measure of the effect of visual distractions on performance.\r\n<h3>Auditory Distractibility</h3>\r\na measure of the effect of auditory distractions on performance.\r\n<h3>Distraction load</h3>\r\na measure of the effect of distraction load on performance.\r\n<h3>Sustained attention</h3>\r\nthe effect of time on performance.', 'What do we actually measure ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '213-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 11:52:46', '2017-12-28 11:52:46', '', 213, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/28/213-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
