 see at home that he/she are having difficulties in this aspect it is advised to refer your child to a specialist in order to understand the reasons behind these difficulties. The reasons are diverse and could be the result of an event your child is experiencing such as Insomnia or a general stressful period, it might be related to attention deficit disorders. The three other indices are related to the performance over time and under Distractor effects. For example we would come to know if your child studies better with Music on…<br />The system will then generate a list of detailed recommendations that will walk you through the implementation of the recommendations and the right way of using them. <br />We suggest that you encourage your child to start with one-two activities at a time, help him make a choice and get him to try it for a week. If this helps him/her function better, that’s great! Reinforce him/her to keep on using it.<br />If he/she picked an activity that didn’t prove to be helpful, skip it and help him/her move to the next activity on the list.<br />If you find any activity unclear enough to apply, please approach the educational team for further guidance.</p><h4><strong>The Child report:</strong></h4><p>The child report has no indices at all, in fact the whole idea here is to communicate with the child in a way that encourages action in the fields that he/she can benefit from.<br />It is best that you assist your child with the report, helping him/her choose easy activities in the beginning, ones that can succeed in order to create a positive motivation for success.</p>', 'parents', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '303-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 08:17:52', '2017-12-28 08:17:52', '', 303, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/28/303-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
