(320, 1, '2017-12-28 08:47:24', '2017-12-28 08:47:24', '\n			<ul>\n				<li title=\"Edit Widget\">\n				</li>\n									<li title=\"Duplicate Widget\">\n						Duplicate Widget\n					</li>\n									<li title=\"Save Widget\">\n						Save Widget\n					</li>\n									<li title=\"Remove Widget\">\n						Remove Widget\n					</li>\n							</ul>\n		<h3>Using the system in a school setting</h3><p>The AXON-School™ system is designed to be used for the entire school once a year. Were the system has been used so far we learn that the cycle of a batch of children performing the test is usually 30 minutes which includes a short intro made by the teacher, logging-in, running through the on-screen instructions, performing a short practice session and finally performing the test.</p><p>This process is very easy to manage, as the system runs automatically through most of the session. As a teacher you will not require any unusual technical skills to operate the system.</p><p>We recommend a maximum number of 20 children per batch, provided that each child has enough space to perform the test without overlooking the monitor of a neighboring child.</p><p>Each child will require a dedicated internet connected PC, a monitor and a headset.</p><p>Results are funneled into the system immediately and automatically.</p>', 'USING THE SYSTEM IN A SCHOOL SETTING', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '319-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 08:47:24', '2017-12-28 08:47:24', '', 319, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/28/319-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(323, 1, '2017-12-28 08:49:53', '2017-12-28 08:49:53', '\n		<p>The AXON-School™ system is designed to be used for the entire school once a year. Where the system has been used so far we learn that the cycle of a batch of children performing the test is usually 30 minutes which includes a short intro made by the teacher, logging-in, running through the on-screen instructions, performing a short practice session and finally performing the test.</p><p>This process is very easy to manage, as the system runs automatically through most of the session. As a teacher you will not require any unusual technical skills to operate the system.</p><p>We recommend a maximum number of 20 children per batch, provided that each child has enough space to perform the test without overlooking the monitor of a neighboring child.</p><p>Each child will require a dedicated internet connected PC, a monitor and a headset.</p><p>Results are funneled into the system immediately and automatically.</p>', 'Using the system in a school setting', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'using-the-system-in-a-school-setting', '', '', '2017-12-31 21:36:15', '2017-12-31 21:36:15', '', 33, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/?page_id=323', 0, 'page', '', 0),
