(325, 1, '2017-12-28 08:51:29', '2017-12-28 08:51:29', '\n		<p>The AXON-School™ system is designed to be used for the entire school once a year. Were the system has been used so far we learn that the cycle of a batch of children performing the test is usually 30 minutes which includes a short intro made by the teacher, logging-in, running through the on-screen instructions, performing a short practice session and finally performing the test.</p><p>This process is very easy to manage, as the system runs automatically through most of the session. As a teacher you will not require any unusual technical skills to operate the system.</p><p>We recommend a maximum number of 20 children per batch, provided that each child has enough space to perform the test without overlooking the monitor of a neighboring child.</p><p>Each child will require a dedicated internet connected PC, a monitor and a headset.</p><p>Results are funneled into the system immediately and automatically.</p>', 'Using the system in a school setting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '323-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 08:51:29', '2017-12-28 08:51:29', '', 323, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/28/323-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
