(440, 1, '2017-12-28 12:37:04', '2017-12-28 12:37:04', '<p><strong>The</strong><b> AXON-School™</b> test measures Attention based indices that have been validated through a clinical trial and standardized to be used in a school setting. Attentiveness, Impulsivity and hyper-reactivity are indices that compare the examinee to other subjects of the same age and gender. The other indices that we present compare the examinee to his baseline performance. </p><h5> </h5>		\n		<img width=\"1024\" height=\"302\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img-1024x302.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img-1024x302.png 1024w, https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img-300x88.png 300w, https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img-768x227.png 768w, https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img.png 1146w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />		\n			<h2>COMPARATIVE MEASURES > ></h2>		\n								<img width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_11.png\" alt=\"\" />							\n													<h3>\n								ATTENTIVENESS							</h3>\n								The ability of the child to correctly evaluate and respond to a stimulus							\n													<h3>\n								 Level of attention							</h3>\n								 ability of the student to respond correctly to the target element and remain focused throughout the test. (measure of sustained attention).							\n								<img width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_22.png\" alt=\"\" />							\n													<h3>\n								Impulsiveness							</h3>\n								The tendency of the child to react the wrong target\n													<h3>\n								Level of Impulsiveness							</h3>\n								(Self-controlled vs. Impulsive) – Measurement of responses to non-targets during the test.							\n								<img width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_33.png\" alt=\"\" />							\n													<h3>\n								Responsiveness 							</h3>\n								Excessive responses to the target element\n													<h3>\n								Level of responsiveness 							</h3>\n								(Responsiveness regulated vs. over responsive) – Measurement of the number of responses the student is making for each target.The thre indices above have been tested in a clinical trial of over 798 children, and were found to have an excellent sensitivity profile of 90% and Specificity of 86%. \n			<h2>Non-Comparative indices:</h2>		\n		<p>The AXON-School™ test makes use of several non-comparative indices related to the performance of the examinee throughout the test in relation to his base performance. This allows us to examine the impact of distractors and time on the student overall performance.</p>		\n                <h3>\n                    Visual Distractibility\n                </h3>\n                <p> a measure of the effect of visual distractions on performance.</p>\n                <h3>\n                    Auditory Distractibility\n                </h3>\n                <p>a measure of the effect of auditory distractions on performance.</p>\n                <h3>\n                    Distraction load\n                </h3>\n                <p>a measure of the effect of distraction load on performance.</p>\n                <h3>\n                    Sustained attention\n                </h3>\n                <p>the effect of time on performance.\n</p>\n		', 'What do we actually measure ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '213-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 12:37:04', '2017-12-28 12:37:04', '', 213, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/28/213-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(441, 1, '2017-12-28 12:38:10', '2017-12-28 12:38:10', '<p><strong>The</strong><b> AXON-School™</b> test measures Attention based indices that have been validated through a clinical trial and standardized to be used in a school setting. Attentiveness, Impulsivity and hyper-reactivity are indices that compare the examinee to other subjects of the same age and gender. The other indices that we present compare the examinee to his baseline performance. </p><h5> </h5>		\n		<img width=\"1024\" height=\"302\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img-1024x302.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img-1024x302.png 1024w, https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img-300x88.png 300w, https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img-768x227.png 768w, https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/img.png 1146w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />		\n			<h2>COMPARATIVE MEASURES > ></h2>		\n								<img width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_11.png\" alt=\"\" />							\n													<h3>\n								ATTENTIVENESS							</h3>\n								The ability of the child to correctly evaluate and respond to a stimulus							\n													<h3>\n								 Level of attention							</h3>\n								 ability of the student to respond correctly to the target element and remain focused throughout the test. (measure of sustained attention).							\n								<img width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_22.png\" alt=\"\" />							\n													<h3>\n								Impulsiveness							</h3>\n								The tendency of the child to react the wrong target\n													<h3>\n								Level of Impulsiveness							</h3>\n								(Self-controlled vs. Impulsive) – Measurement of responses to non-targets during the test.							\n								<img width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_33.png\" alt=\"\" />							\n													<h3>\n								Responsiveness 							</h3>\n								Excessive responses to the target element\n													<h3>\n								Level of responsiveness 							</h3>\n								(Responsiveness regulated vs. over responsive) – Measurement of the number of responses the student is making for each target.The thre indices above have been tested in a clinical trial of over 798 children, and were found to have an excellent sensitivity profile of 90% and Specificity of 86%. \n			<h2>Non-Comparative indices:</h2>		\n		<p>The AXON-School™ test makes use of several non-comparative indices related to the performance of the examinee throughout the test in relation to his base performance. This allows us to examine the impact of distractors and time on the student overall performance.</p>		\n                <h3>\n                    Visual Distractibility\n                </h3>\n                <p> a measure of the effect of visual distractions on performance.</p>\n                <h3>\n                    Auditory Distractibility\n                </h3>\n                <p>a measure of the effect of auditory distractions on performance.</p>\n                <h3>\n                    Distraction load\n                </h3>\n                <p>a measure of the effect of distraction load on performance.</p>\n                <h3>\n                    Sustained attention\n                </h3>\n                <p>the effect of time on performance.\n</p>\n		', 'What do we actually measure ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '213-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 12:38:10', '2017-12-28 12:38:10', '', 213, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/28/213-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(442, 1, '2017-12-28 12:39:37', '2017-12-28 12:39:37', '\n					<h3>\n							Testing the attentional <br>capabilities <br>\n					</h3>\n			<a href=\"https://app.axon-school.com/demo\" target=\"_blank\">\n						FREE TRIAL\n					</a>\n			<a href=\"https://app.axon-school.com/login\" target=\"_blank\">\n						login\n					</a>\n		https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JolA8uYBC3g		\n					<h3>\n							Testing the attentional <br>capabilities <br>\n					</h3>\n			<a href=\"#\">\n						FREE TRIAL\n					</a>\n			<a href=\"https://app.axon-school.com/login\" target=\"_blank\">\n						login\n					</a>\n		https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JolA8uYBC3g		\n					<h3>\n					</h3>\n						\"The AXON-School is a good exercise to know your class and the children in it. Using this tool we can work as a school to improve the students\' performance. In order to better understand the child, the teacher should be fully equipped with the reports as attention span is very important in today\'s life for getting better results\"	\nThe Millennium School, Gurgaon, India.					\n					<cite>Educational team memberThe Millennium School, Gurgaon, India.</cite>				\n						<img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/tt_1.png\" alt=\"Educational team member\">\n						\"It is important to know about our own attention – it helps us in certain ways. I want to find ways to improve my attention\"\n					<cite>Hylav pratavsi StudentThe Millennium School, Gurgaon, India.</cite>				\n						<img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/tt_3.png\" alt=\"Hylav pratavsi Student\">\n						\"We see AXON-School as a professional educational tool. Axon-School helps the educational team overachieve educational targets in a professional and measurable way, giving us the ability to advance every student and maximize his or hers abilities\"	\n					<cite>Mrs. Levana Milon School principleMofet Ramot Alon, Jerusalem, Israel.</cite>				\n						<img src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/