(458, 1, '2017-12-31 21:36:15', '2017-12-31 21:36:15', '\n		<p>The AXON-School™ system is designed to be used for the entire school once a year. Where the system has been used so far we learn that the cycle of a batch of children performing the test is usually 30 minutes which includes a short intro made by the teacher, logging-in, running through the on-screen instructions, performing a short practice session and finally performing the test.</p><p>This process is very easy to manage, as the system runs automatically through most of the session. As a teacher you will not require any unusual technical skills to operate the system.</p><p>We recommend a maximum number of 20 children per batch, provided that each child has enough space to perform the test without overlooking the monitor of a neighboring child.</p><p>Each child will require a dedicated internet connected PC, a monitor and a headset.</p><p>Results are funneled into the system immediately and automatically.</p>', 'Using the system in a school setting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '323-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-31 21:36:15', '2017-12-31 21:36:15', '', 323, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/31/323-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(459, 1, '2017-12-31 21:37:43', '2017-12-31 21:37:43', '<h2><strong>\"…the greatest act of love is to pay Attention\".</strong></h2><p><strong><em>–Diane Sawyer-</em></strong></p><p>Many cognitive researchers describe Attention as a \"light projector\". We as operators direct the beam of light to the subject of our interest bringing it to focus. Naturally this much focus doesn\'t leave room for all the other objects around and so many of them are kept in darkness, sometimes ignored and sometimes even critical information is lost because of that. <br />But, what happens if this projector is not functioning well,</p><p> if there are disturbances to the normal flow of attention and our ability to focus it?</p>		\n		<p>Let\'s first observe the reasons that may cause a reduction of Attention, the following is only a short list of reasons for the reduction of attention as they may materialize at school:</p>		\n		<img width=\"130\" height=\"130\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_6.png\" alt=\"\" />		\n			<h2>External reasons </h2>		\n		<ul><li>Interruptions by other students</li><li>General noises in class or outside the classroom</li><li>Sitting at the back of the</li><li>classroom (if visually distracted).</li></ul>		\n		<img width=\"130\" height=\"130\" src=\"https://axon.digitalim.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/icon_7.png\" alt=\"\" />		\n			<h2>INTERNAL reasons </h2>		\n		<ul><li>Sleeping problems</li><li>lack of motivation / boredom</li><li>Stress</li><li>General illness</li><li>Social problems</li></ul><p>Naturally some of the reasons for a reduction in attentional capabilities are related to cognitive deficiencies or Mental disorders. These can include: Depression, Anxiety, learning disability, Autism and ADHD.</p><p>For most people refocusing attention is a relatively easy task, as easy as redirecting a light projector, but for others, especially for people with attentional disorders, such as ADHD, this task is extremely hard, and is often a cause of substantial distress.</p><p>Neurotech Solutions is a world leader on the field of ADHD diagnosis, if this is a subject of interest for you , additional information can be found on a dedicated site:<br />  <a href=\"http://www.neurotech-solutions.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">www.neurotech-solutions.com</a> </p>		\n		<h3>The different skills of Attention:</h3><p>Attention is in fact far more complex than initially conceived. We know today through the pathology of attentional disorders, that Attention is a collection of abilities. The verdict is still open on whether or not these abilities are stable or if they could be changed, but for sure, a person can learn how to overcome his limitations and sometimes even turn these into advantages, some very successful people, claim to attribute their success to their ADHD.</p><p>By applying a simple computerized test in the form of a computer game, AXON-School™, Neurotech\'s newest product, breaks down Attention to its most relevant components to build an attentional profile for each student, later used to help students identify their short comings and strengths.</p>', 'Attention in a glimpse', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '285-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-31 21:37:43', '2017-12-31 21:37:43', '', 285, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/31/285-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(460, 1, '2017-12-31 21:41:48', '2017-12-31 21:41:48', '\n		<h4><strong>The feeling of the report</strong></h4><p>So your child completed the AXON-School ™ test and now you get the results of this test. The results can be delivered to you by your child\'s teacher, sent to you by e-mail or through your child, based on a decision made in your child\'s school.<br />Your child\'s teacher received a report explaining how to improve your child\'s abilities in the classroom and you and your child also received reports as well, based on the same test.<br />A parent report will provide you with a glimpse into your child\'s world of attention in a way that will help you understand him / her better, and a list of recommendations you apply at home related to studies, friends, hobbies,<br />The child report offers the child an opportunity to learn about himself / herself in a constructive manner, and to prevent them from acting. Let\'s take a closer look at the reports:</p><h4><strong>Parent Report:</strong></h4><p>Children are not born with a guide, and like every child it is very different from the next. It will be okay to give general guidance on how to motivate the child to support their psychological development and even to deal with their physical safety. Including more. The attention capabilities as presented to you by the The AXON-School™ test are an important keyhole to your child\'s situation along with the recommendation we provide you within the report, you can make a significant difference to your child\'s health.</p>		\n		<h4><strong>Let\'s start from looking at the way the results are described to you. </strong></h4><p><strong>Three indices:</strong> Attentiveness, Self-control and Hyper-reactivity are comparative indices, this means that your child has been compared to many other children of the same age and gender (norms). The result here can be below average, average and above average. If the system identified your child as having below average performance and you see at home that he/she are having difficulties in this aspect it is advised to refer your child to a specialist in order to understand the reasons behind these difficulties. The reasons are diverse and could be the result of an event your child is experiencing such as Insomnia or a general stressful period, it might be related to attention deficit disorders. The three other indices are related to the performance over time and under Distractor effects. For example we would come to know if your child studies better with Music on…<br />The system will then generate a list of detailed recommendations that will walk you through the implementation of the recommendations and the right way of using them. <br />We suggest that you encourage your child to start with one-two activities at a time, help him make a choice and get him to try it for a week. If this helps him/her function better, that’s great! Reinforce him/her to keep on using it.<br />If he/she picked an activity that didn’t prove to be helpful, skip it and help him/her move to the next activity on the list.<br />If you find any activity unclear enough to apply, please approach the educational team for further guidance.</p><h4><strong>The Child report:</strong></h4><p>The child report has no indices at all, in fact the whole idea here is to communicate with the child in a way that encourages action in the fields that he/she can benefit from.<br />It is best that you assist your child with the report, helping him/her choose easy activities in the beginning, ones that can succeed in order to create a positive motivation for success.</p>', 'Making sense of the report', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '303-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-31 21:41:48', '2017-12-31 21:41:48', '', 303, 'https://axon.digitalim.co.il/2017/12/31/303-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
